# 02 Review of Motor System
## Repeating
1. False statement with regard to the **corticobulbar tract**
	- **Indirect pathway from primary motor cortex to spinal cord** #B23
	- **Synapse with Anterior Horn Cells of Spinal Cord** #B22
	- Begins in motor cortex
	- Synapse with cranial nerve motor nuclei
	- Fibers leave pyramidal pathway at several levels
2. Location of the **decussated** fibers of the Corticospinal Tract in the spinal cord #B23  #B22 
	- Answer: **Lateral Funniculus**
	- Explanation: Decussated fibers refer to the **lateral CST** which is located at the lateral funniculus while the non-decussated refers to the **anterior CST** found in the anterior funniculus

## Important Notes
```ad-important
title: Infarctions

**MCA infarction** results in contralateral paralysis of arm and face

**ACA infarction** results in contralateral paresis of the lower extremities

```

```ad-important
title: Cerebellum vs. Basal Ganglia Disorders

**Cerebellum:** Awkward intentional movements ipsilateral to the lesion

**Basal Ganglia:** Unexpected meaningless unintentional movements contralateral to lesion
```

### Corticospinal Tract
- Arrangement of fibers from medial to lateral: **cervical, thoracic, lumbar, sacral**
```mermaid
graph TD
	subgraph Cerebrum
	A[Motor Cortex]--converge-->B[Corona Radiata]
	B--Pass Inferiorly-->C[Posterior Internal Capsule]
	end
	
	subgraph Brainstem
	C-->D[Cerebral Peduncles of Midbrain]
	D-->E[Pons]
	E-->F[Medulla]
	end
	
	subgraph Spinal Cord
	F--Decussates in Anterior Aspect-->G[Lateral CST]
	F--Does not Decussate-->H[Anterior CST]
	G & H --> I[Anterior Gray Horn of Spinal Cord]
	I-->J[Ventral Root]
	end
	J-->K[Peripheral Nerves]
	
```

### Corticobulbar Tract
- Only **cranial nerves I, II, and VII** do not synapse with this tract as they are ==purely sensory==
![Pasted image 20220402095924.png](data:image/png;base64,)

### Indirect Pathways
| Tract                    | Origin                         | Function                                                             |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Rubrospinal              | Red Nucleus (Rostral Midbrain) | **Distal flexors** of the arms and hands                                 |
| Vestibulospinal          | Vestibular Nuclei (Medulla)    | Reflex control of **posture and balance**; Coordination of eye movements |
| Medullary Reticulospinal | Reticular Formation            | Predominantly inhibition of segmental **reflexes**                       |
| Pontine Reticulospinal   | Reticular Formation            | Stimulate **extensor** and inhibit flexor                                |
| Tectospinal              | Superior Colliculus (Midbrain) | Coordination of **head and eye** movements                               |

![Pasted image 20220402102207.png](data:image/png;base64,)

### Motor Neurons
| Neuron | Corticospinal Tract              | Corticobulbar Tract         |
|:------:| -------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
|  UMN   | Motor neurons in cerebral cortex       | Motor neurons in cerebral cortex |
|  LMN   | Anterior horn cells of Spinal Cord| Cranial nerve motor nuclei of brainstem                                 |

| Characteristic            | UMN             | LMN                                                   |
| ------------------------- | --------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Muscles affected          | In groups       | Individual                                            |
| Atrophy                   | Disuse (slight) | Denervation (severe)                                  |
| Babinski                  | Positive        | Negative                                              |
| Tendon Reflexes           | Hyperactive     | Hypoactive or Absent                                  |
| Resulting Paralysis       | Spastic         | Flaccid                                               |
| Fasciculations            | Absent          | Present                                               |
| Electromyography   | Normal          | Abnormal (fibrillation, fasciculation, + sharp waves) |
| Nerve Conduction Velocity | Normal          | Abnormal (Denervation Potential)                                                      |

### Reflexes
|     Characteristic      | Stretch (Muscle Spindle)                   | GTO                           |
|:-----------------------:| ------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
|        Position         | Parallel to muscle fibers | Distal end of muscle          |
|        Synapses         | Monosynaptic              | Disynaptic                    |
|        Stimulus         | Stretch to muscle spindle | Tension to golgi tendon organ |
| Causative Muscle Action | Stretching                | Contraction                   |
| Resulting Muscle Action | Contraction               | Relaxation                    |
